<h1 class="ds-page-title">Dates</h1>
<p class="ds-page-lead">
    Dates should be formatted consistently throughout COMPASS. Use full month names in stat cards and abbreviated month names in tables.
</p>

<h2>Date formatting rules</h2>
<p>
    COMPASS uses specific date formats depending on the context. Never use numeric date formats (e.g., 01/06/2026 or 18/06/1981).
</p>

<h2>Stat cards format</h2>
<p>
    In stat cards and other prominent displays, use the format: <strong>D MMMM YYYY</strong>
</p>
<p>
    This means: Day number (no leading zero) + Full month name + Full year
</p>

<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Stat card dates</div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card dfe-adminui-border-left-primary shadow h-100">
                <div class="dfe-adminui-card__body">
                    <div class="row no-gutters align-items-center">
                        <div class="col mr-2">
                            <div class="text-xs font-weight-bold text-primary text-uppercase mb-1">Last updated</div>
                            <div class="h5 mb-0 font-weight-bold text-gray-800">1 June 2026</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-auto">
                            <i class="fas fa-calendar fa-2x text-gray-300"></i>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card dfe-adminui-border-left-success shadow h-100">
                <div class="dfe-adminui-card__body">
                    <div class="row no-gutters align-items-center">
                        <div class="col mr-2">
                            <div class="text-xs font-weight-bold text-success text-uppercase mb-1">Due date</div>
                            <div class="h5 mb-0 font-weight-bold text-gray-800">18 June 2026</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-auto">
                            <i class="fas fa-calendar-check fa-2x text-gray-300"></i>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card dfe-adminui-border-left-info shadow h-100">
                <div class="dfe-adminui-card__body">
                    <div class="row no-gutters align-items-center">
                        <div class="col mr-2">
                            <div class="text-xs font-weight-bold text-info text-uppercase mb-1">Created</div>
                            <div class="h5 mb-0 font-weight-bold text-gray-800">15 January 2025</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-auto">
                            <i class="fas fa-calendar-plus fa-2x text-gray-300"></i>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Correct examples for stat cards</h3>
<ul>
    <li>1 June 2026</li>
    <li>18 June 2026</li>
    <li>15 January 2025</li>
    <li>3 December 2024</li>
    <li>31 March 2025</li>
</ul>

<h3>Incorrect examples (never use)</h3>
<ul>
    <li>01/06/2026</li>
    <li>18/06/1981</li>
    <li>01-06-2026</li>
    <li>2026-06-01</li>
    <li>06/01/2026</li>
</ul>

<h2>Tables format</h2>
<p>
    In tables and compact displays, use the format: <strong>D MMM YYYY</strong>
</p>
<p>
    This means: Day number (no leading zero) + Abbreviated month name + Full year
</p>

<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Table dates</div>
    <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Project</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Created</th>
                <th>Due date</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Project Alpha</td>
                <td><span class="dfe-adminui-badge dfe-adminui-badge--success">Active</span></td>
                <td>1 Jun 2026</td>
                <td>18 Jun 2026</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Project Beta</td>
                <td><span class="dfe-adminui-badge dfe-adminui-badge--warning">Pending</span></td>
                <td>15 Jan 2025</td>
                <td>3 Dec 2025</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Project Gamma</td>
                <td><span class="dfe-adminui-badge dfe-adminui-badge--info">In progress</span></td>
                <td>31 Mar 2025</td>
                <td>30 Apr 2025</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<h3>Correct examples for tables</h3>
<ul>
    <li>1 Jun 2026</li>
    <li>18 Jun 2026</li>
    <li>15 Jan 2025</li>
    <li>3 Dec 2024</li>
    <li>31 Mar 2025</li>
</ul>

<h3>Month abbreviations</h3>
<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Month abbreviations for table format</div>
    <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Full month</th>
                <th>Abbreviation</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>January</td><td>Jan</td></tr>
            <tr><td>February</td><td>Feb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>March</td><td>Mar</td></tr>
            <tr><td>April</td><td>Apr</td></tr>
            <tr><td>May</td><td>May</td></tr>
            <tr><td>June</td><td>Jun</td></tr>
            <tr><td>July</td><td>Jul</td></tr>
            <tr><td>August</td><td>Aug</td></tr>
            <tr><td>September</td><td>Sep</td></tr>
            <tr><td>October</td><td>Oct</td></tr>
            <tr><td>November</td><td>Nov</td></tr>
            <tr><td>December</td><td>Dec</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Stat cards:</strong> Always use D MMMM YYYY format (e.g., 1 June 2026)</li>
    <li><strong>Tables:</strong> Always use D MMM YYYY format (e.g., 1 Jun 2026)</li>
    <li><strong>Never use:</strong> Numeric formats like 01/06/2026, 18/06/1981, or 2026-06-01</li>
    <li><strong>Day numbers:</strong> Do not use leading zeros (use "1" not "01")</li>
    <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> Use the same format throughout the same page or feature</li>
    <li><strong>Year:</strong> Always include the full 4-digit year</li>
</ul>

<h2>Implementation examples</h2>

<h3>C# / Razor</h3>
<pre><code>@* Stat card format *@
@Model.CreatedDate.ToString("d MMMM yyyy")
@* Output: 1 June 2026 *@

@* Table format *@
@Model.CreatedDate.ToString("d MMM yyyy")
@* Output: 1 Jun 2026 *@</code></pre>

<h3>JavaScript</h3>
<pre><code>// Stat card format
const statCardDate = date.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { 
    day: 'numeric', 
    month: 'long', 
    year: 'numeric' 
});
// Output: 1 June 2026

// Table format
const tableDate = date.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { 
    day: 'numeric', 
    month: 'short', 
    year: 'numeric' 
});
// Output: 1 Jun 2026</code></pre>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use semantic date formats that are clear and unambiguous</li>
    <li>Avoid formats that could be misinterpreted (e.g., 01/06/2026 could be January 6th or June 1st)</li>
    <li>Ensure dates are readable by screen readers</li>
    <li>Use consistent formatting within the same context</li>
</ul>

<h2>Common mistakes to avoid</h2>
<ul>
    <li>❌ Using numeric formats: 01/06/2026, 18/06/1981</li>
    <li>❌ Using leading zeros on day numbers: 01 June 2026 (should be 1 June 2026)</li>
    <li>❌ Mixing formats on the same page</li>
    <li>❌ Using 2-digit years: 1 Jun 26 (should be 1 Jun 2026)</li>
    <li>❌ Using table format in stat cards or vice versa</li>
</ul>
